  "text": "This inventory catalogs all Java source files in Apache Kafka 4.x (version-pinned snapshot github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489) containing @Deprecated annotations on producer/streams configuration constants and exception-handling APIs. The migration involves transitioning from deprecated methods and configuration constants to their newer counterparts.\n\n**StreamsConfig.java** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsConfig.java) contains 26 deprecated symbols including:\n- Configuration constants for cache buffering: CACHE_MAX_BYTES_BUFFERING_CONFIG (since 3.4, use STATESTORE_CACHE_MAX_BYTES_CONFIG instead)\n- Exception handler class configurations: DEFAULT_DESERIALIZATION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG and DEFAULT_PRODUCTION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG (since 4.0, use DESERIALIZATION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG and PRODUCTION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG instead)\n- DSL store configuration: DEFAULT_DSL_STORE_CONFIG (since 3.7, use DSL_STORE_SUPPLIERS_CLASS_CONFIG instead) with related constants ROCKS_DB, IN_MEMORY, and DEFAULT_DSL_STORE\n- Windowed serialization configuration: WINDOWED_INNER_CLASS_SERDE (since 4.1.0, use windowed serializer/deserializer class-specific configuration)\n- Window size configuration: WINDOW_SIZE_MS_CONFIG (since 4.1.0, use TimeWindowedDeserializer#WINDOW_SIZE_MS_CONFIG)\n- Methods: defaultDeserializationExceptionHandler() and defaultProductionExceptionHandler() (since 4.0, use deserializationExceptionHandler() and productionExceptionHandler() instead)\n- Documentation strings for various configs marked as deprecated\n\n**TopicConfig.java** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/config/TopicConfig.java) contains 2 deprecated symbols:\n- MESSAGE_DOWNCONVERSION_ENABLE_CONFIG and MESSAGE_DOWNCONVERSION_ENABLE_DOC (deprecated because down-conversion is not possible in Kafka 4.0+ and will be removed in Kafka 5.0)\n\n**Exception Handler Interfaces and Implementations:**\n- **ProductionExceptionHandler.java** defines two deprecated method signatures:\n  - handle(ProducerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record, Exception exception) (since 3.9, use handle(ErrorHandlerContext context, ProducerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record, Exception exception))\n  - handleSerializationException(ProducerRecord record, Exception exception) (since 3.9, use handleSerializationException(ErrorHandlerContext context, ProducerRecord record, Exception exception, SerializationExceptionOrigin origin))\n- **DefaultProductionExceptionHandler.java** overrides the deprecated handle() method signature\n- **DeserializationExceptionHandler.java** defines a deprecated method signature:\n  - handle(ProcessorContext context, ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record, Exception exception) (since 3.9, use handle(ErrorHandlerContext context, ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]> record, Exception exception))\n- **LogAndFailExceptionHandler.java** and **LogAndContinueExceptionHandler.java** both implement the deprecated handle() method signature from DeserializationExceptionHandler\n\n**TopologyConfig.java** contains one deprecated method:\n- parseStoreType() (marked deprecated in version 4.1.0)\n\nThe migration pattern shows a consistent evolution from context-agnostic handler methods (using ProcessorContext) to a more uniform ErrorHandlerContext-based approach, and from deprecated configuration constants to newer, more explicit alternatives following Kafka's 4.x API improvements."
